RODIMUS nodded grimly as he moved along the path towards the dig site
that was not too far away. By passing the village for the moment they
arrived in short order.

Pointing at the hole that PERCEPTOR had dug when he had escaped
RODIMUS nodded. "I see your handy work there." He said in grimly
humorous tones. "If you can widen that we can see about getting
inside."

As RODIMUS spoke the area got really quiet. The birds stopped singing
and the even the wind seemed to go silent.

It was as if they were being watched.

(TAG)

- Preston
